# [[w:Erhua|儿化韵 (Erhua)]], the addition of a final [[retroflex]] ("ér") to Mandarin syllable (feature of northern Mandarin)

====Usage notes====
Erhua is mainly used in Beijing and northern dialects.
:: [[事儿]], [[瓶儿]], [[公园儿]], [[把儿]]
This pronouciation is not [[w:Standard_Chinese|standard Mandarin]]. But there is some case where the Erhua is used in standard Mandarin.
:: [[这儿]], [[哪儿]], [[一点儿]]
Sometimes, peoples from the south of China have difficulty to pronouce the Erhua. So they prefer to use [[这里]] / [[那里]] instead of [[这儿]] / [[哪儿]] and [[一下]] instead of [[一会儿]].
 
In some case, the Erhua can change the meaning of a word.
* [[头]] head  -> [[头儿]] leader
*  [[白面]] flour -> [[白面儿]] heroine

